C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wlq1665702804353.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wlq1665702804353.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wlq1665702804353.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wlq1665702804353\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      New Implementation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Add new implementation for this component\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__p_d6329e1_d6330e1_d6331e1\">A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the other non-Uniface implementations.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__p_d6332e1_d6333e1_d6334e1\">You cannot create a Uniface implementation if the component name exceeds 16 bytes.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__section_kbk_vhf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d524493e61\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__ul_dn4_vhf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__li_d3119e1_d3120e1_d3121e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hip1665702803864.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hip1665702803864.html\" title=\"Implementation type defined or available for the component.\">Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__li_d3122e1_d3123e1_d3124e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prp1665702665837.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prp1665702665837.html\" title=\"Determines whether the new implementation should use the description and comments defined in the component's specification.\">Option: Copy Description and Comments</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__section_wnz_vhf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d524493e88\">How to</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wlq1665702804353__p_d6380e1_d6381e1_d6382e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zzx1665702678830.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" title=\"Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.\">Define a Component Signature</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kqj1665702890051.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Implementations</a><p>The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423863\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423863\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "New Implementation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 New Implementation Add new implementation for this component A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the other non-Uniface implementations. You cannot create a Uniface implementation if the component name exceeds 16 bytes. Fields Type Option: Copy Description and Comments How to Define a Component Signature Related Links Component Implementations The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}